Anonymous Fri 31 May 2024 23:00:12 No.66215040 Report

>>66214504
This will take some explaining of the setting

So the basic idea is that humanity made God, or at least a machine that acted like it, like a more benevolent AM from IHNMAIMS. After humanity (Known as the precursors in the modern day) drove itself extinct, it took to rebuilding mankind using the various data records and samples it had stored with it, with the aid of synthetic people (known as angels) it could manufacture. This led to 2 types of "Human" after years of combined progress

Karhat are failed attempts to remake man. It's comprised of Anthros and such, and they make up 90% of the populace. Trueborn are what we would call human, and they make up for their lack of natural abilities with the ingrained ability to use precurser technology

The angels were wrapped in a civil war during this period. Some of them believed that they shouldn't be tied down to a civilisation that destroyed itself, and that it wasn't worth recreating and protecting over making their own destiny. These fallen angels exist to this day, and while they can create more synth shells, they lack the ability to make them act and think like God could. Because of this, they abduct people, extract their brains into tubes, make them less sentient via a steady chemical alteration (A process known as the numbing) and then have them wirelessly control a synth shell as a soldier, assassin, what have you. They are known as the Chosen

Vee is one of these, she's only become sentient again since the site her brain was at was hit by a solar flare and now works on backup power. keeping the brain alive but not continuing the numbing process. Now she lives as a drifting bounty hunter, constantly hunted herself by other Chosen, which is why she can't stay in one place for too long
